<document>
	<title>The adrenal cortex in cystic fibrosis of the pancreas.</title>

	<author>Hawkins-E.</author>
	<author>Singer-D-B.</author>

	<source>Am-J-Clin-Pathol. 1976 Oct. 66(4). P 710-4.</source>

	<abstract>The morphologies of the adrenal cortical zones of 25 children with
   cystic fibrosis and 24 control patients are presented. A technic for
   objective measurement of these zones is described. Hyperplasia of the
   zona glomerulosa in the children with cystic fibrosis is significant
   and may be related to chronic loss of salt in the sweat or demands
   placed on renal salt-conserving mechanisms.</abstract>

